Definition: a militant Marxist-Leninist terrorist organization formed in 1975 to force Turkey to acknowledge killing more than a million Armenians and forcibly removing them from border areas in 1915
Example: wants Turkey to pay reparations and cede territory to Armenia; ASALA bombing at Orly Airport in Paris in 1983 killed 8 and wounded 55 people
Synonyms: ASALA, Orly_Group, rd_October_Organization, terrorist_organization, i, noun, act, terrorism, c, location, Armenia, r, a, militant, Marxist-Leninist, terrorist, organization, formed, in, to, force, Turkey, acknowledge, killing, more, than, million, Armenians, and, forcibly, removing, them, from, border, areas, wants, pay, reparations, cede, territory, bombing, at, Orly, Airport, Paris, killed, wounded, people
Category: noun.group
